  "prompt": "When will I start the preparation of ilts?",
  "response": "The timing for starting your preparation for the ILTS (Illinois Licensure Testing System) exams depends on several factors, including your current knowledge and proficiency in the subject areas covered by the exams, your study habits, and your target test date. Here are some general guidelines to help you determine when to start preparing:\n\n1. **Assess Your Current Knowledge:** Evaluate how familiar you are with the content areas of the ILTS exams you need to take. If you have a strong background, you might need less time to prepare.\n\n2. **Set a Target Test Date:** Determine when you plan to take the ILTS exams. Working backward from this date will help you create a study schedule.\n\n3. **Create a Study Plan:** Based on your assessment and target test date, create a study plan that includes the topics you need to cover, resources you'll use, and a timeline. This plan should allow for regular studying and review sessions.\n\n4. **Consider Your Schedule:** Take into account your personal and professional commitments. Ensure you allocate enough time for effective preparation without overwhelming yourself.\n\n5. **Start Early:** It's generally better to start your preparation early to avoid last-minute cramming and to give yourself ample time to understand and review the material thoroughly.\n\nAs a rough guideline, many candidates begin their preparation several months before their intended test date. For example, if you plan to take the ILTS exams in six months, starting your preparation now would be a good idea.\n\nUltimately, the best time to start preparing is when you can dedicate consistent and focused effort to your studies, ensuring you feel confident and well-prepared by the time of your exams.",
